BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED
CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY
TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY
RELAYED BY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE AUSTIN/SAN ANTONIO TX
1047 PM CDT FRI SEP 24 2021

THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS
DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY.

THE BAY CITY ISD POLICE DEPARTMENT IS SEARCHING FOR ALICITY EREVIA,
HISPANIC, FEMALE, 17 YEARS OLD, 5 FOOT TALL, 180 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR,
BROWN EYES, AND LAST SEEN WEARING A BLACK ADIDAS JACKET WITH WHITE
STRIPES AND BLUE JEANS. 

POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR SHARRIEFF SHARRIEFF, BLACK, MALE, 22 YEARS
OLD, 6 FOOT TALL, 185 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR, BROWN EYES, IN CONNECTION
WITH HER ABDUCTION.

THE SUSPECT IS DRIVING A BLACK, 2017, DODGE, RAM WITH A TEXAS 
LICENSE PLATE NUMBER OF P T D 4 6 2 9.

THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM IN THE 400 BLOCK OF 7TH STREET, BAY
CITY, TEXAS.

LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THIS CHILD TO BE IN GRAVE OR
IMMEDIATE DANGER. 

IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE BAY
CITY ISD POLICE DEPARTMENT.

NEWS MEDIA POINT OF CONTACT IS BAY CITY ISD POLICE DEPARTMENT AT 9 7
9 2 3 6 6 9 0 5.


$$
